#Text=Charlotte Rose
#Text=Charlotte
#Text=Rose
#Text=is an English sex worker , dominatrix , sexual trainer and political candidate from Nottingham , [ 1 ] who lives in London . [ 2 ]
#Text=In 2013 she won the award of " Sex Worker of the Year " at the Sexual Freedom Awards where she is now a resident judge . [ 2 ] [ 3 ]

column1: #Text=In 2014 she took up politics , campaigning for sexual freedom as an independent candidate in the Clacton and Rochester and Strood by-elections . [ 4 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=Career
#Text=Rose began her career in the sex industry at the age of 17 where she took part in a dominatrix-themed photoshoot . [ 1 ]
#Text=Rose married and became the mother of two children , one elder son and one younger daughter . [ 2 ]
#Text=She became a teacher , but after separating from her partner she moved to Exeter , Devon in 2003 and decided to become an escort .
#Text=She became a vocal supporter of the sex industry . [ 2 ]
#Text=Rose also said that she wants to become Britain 's number one sex guru . [ 1 ]
#Text=In 2013 she won the " British Erotic Award for Sex Worker of the Year " .

#Text=Following this appearance Rose claimed she was the victim of a hate campaign , which resulted in her landlord evicting her and having to move to London .
#Text=Rose claimed : " What other reason would it be apart from my profession ? I do n't do any harm , I do n't make noise and I am just normal .

#Text=However , the programme led to criticism from some viewers , who accused Rose of  glamourizing " her profession .

column1: #Text=It also led to accusations on social media against Rose 's partner , a builder and author of erotic literature , that he was profiting from her earnings .
#Text=Rose and her partner both refuted these allegations . [ 8 ]
#Text=In 2015
#Text=Rose performed in a run of The Sex Workers ' Opera at London 's Pleasance Theatre . [ 9 ]
#Text=The show , which included elements of opera , hip hop and poetry to tell women 's stories , went on its first UK tour in 2017 . [ 10 ] [ 11 ]
#Text=Politics
#Text=In 2014
#Text=Rose began to stand in political elections , campaigning for sexual freedom .
#Text=She has stood as an independent candidate , but the Sexual Freedom Coalition lists her as standing for the " Sexual Freedom Party " . [ 12 ]

column1: #Text=Rose first stood in the Clacton by-election on 9 October 2014 .
#Text=Out of eight candidates she finished last , taking 56 votes ( 0.16 % of the vote ) . [ 4 ]
#Text=Rose then stood in the Rochester and Strood by-election .
#Text=Out of thirteen candidates Rose finished eleventh , taking 43 votes ( 0.11 % ) . [ 5 ]
#Text=On 12 December 2014 , Rose organised a protest against the Audiovisual Media Services Regulations 2014 amendment to the Communications Act 2003 .
#Text=One of the practices banned was facesitting , so part of the protest was a mass facesitting with people singing " Sit on My Face " by Monty Python . [ 13 ]
#Text=On 1 March 2015 she organised a public spanking event at Manchester 's Sackville Gardens , also as a protest against the legislation . [ 14 ]
#Text=In 2016
#Text=Rose gave evidence to the Home Affairs Select Committee , which was looking at the way sex work is treated by legislation . [ 15 ] [ 16 ]

#Text=The Committee backed calls to change the rules regarding brothel-keeping and completely decriminalise sex work , though no legislation has been brought before Parliament to act on their recommendations . [ 17 ]
